article.description: Jasmine James scored 14 points, Meredith Mitchell added 12 and Georgia stormed back from an 11-0 deficit to beat Arkansas 57-54 in overtime.
article.headline: Georgia overcomes early 11-0 deficit to beat Arkansas
article.linkText: Georgia rallies from 11 down to beat Arkansas
article.story:
ATHENS, Ga. --  Jasmine James scored 14 points, Meredith Mitchell added 12 and Georgia (No. 24 AP) stormed back from an 11-0 deficit to beat Arkansas 57-54 in overtime on Thursday night.

Porsha Phillips pulled down 18 rebounds, one shy of her career high, for the Lady Bulldogs (17-5, 7-2 Southeastern Conference), who put up a season low for points in the first half with 20.

Lyndsay Harris scored 22 points and Sarah Watkins had 16 points and 14 rebounds for the Razorbacks (16-6, 4-6).
